         <abstract>
            <p>Use of a "risk" questionnaire can facilitate a dialogue between investment managers and institutional clients on the topic of risk tolerance. The questionnaire is designed in such a way that a respondent's indication of interest in various topics also indicates the respondent's risk-taking propensities. Such information allows managers to tailor their services to the particular needs of individual clients.</p>
